shortcut in python 

python3 -m venv myenv  ==> to create a virtual env with name as myenv
source myenv/bin/activate  ==> to activate the virtual env



#*to create kernel in vs code*
pip install jupyter ==> to add to your virtual env
jupyter notebook --generate-config  ==> to create config file for notebook
nano ~/.jupyter/jupyter_notebook_config.py  ==>  to open nano text editor 

#inside this find the below and make changes

## The directory to use for notebooks and kernels.
#over there add this 
c.NotebookApp.notebook_dir = 'path of your directory'

and save and exit 
and then restart your ide



